snippet.textDisplay: Food for thought...one could argue the Lakers have played and will play the hardest schedule in the NBA. Anytime you are the top contender with the biggest stars on your team, not only do other title contenders circle their calendar for the games against the Lakers, but also, the lesser teams that won't make the playoffs, they circle the games against the Lakers on their calendar because it's their opportunity to prove themselves and be measured against the best team, which is a very valuable assessment that is very necessary in future contract negotiations...BASICALLY, THE LAKERS GET EVERYBODY'S "A" GAME🤔
